# Bitcoin Market Sentiment and Trader Performance Analysis

## Project Overview

This project analyzes the relationship between Bitcoin market sentiment and trader performance using the Fear & Greed Index and Hyperliquid trading data.

## Tools Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib

## Key Findings

- Fear generated the highest trading activity.
- Extreme Greed produced the highest average profit per trade.
- Fear generated the highest cumulative profit.
- Larger positions were taken during Fear periods.
- Selling activity increased during Greed and Extreme Greed.

## Project Structure

- Data Cleaning
- Data Merging
- Exploratory Data Analysis
- Visualization
- Business Insights

## Results

The analysis demonstrates that market sentiment significantly impacts trading behavior and profitability.
